timeline

    title Maintainability Trajectory — How Code Health Evolves Over a Module's Lifecycle

    section Stage 0 &mdash; Greenfield
        Initial implementation : Targets defined per sub-characteristic
                               : Cyclomatic complexity ≤ 8 for 95% of functions
                               : Test coverage ≥ 80% on critical paths
                               : Module entered into per-module target matrix

    section Stage 1 &mdash; Feature absorption
        First major feature lands : Complexity drift +5 to +15
                                  : Test coverage may dip ~5%
                                  : Trajectory marked as "absorbing change"
                                  : No suppressions added

    section Stage 2 &mdash; Recalibration
        Refactor sprint scheduled : Targets reviewed against change velocity
                                 : Per-module matrix updated if velocity shifted
                                 : Refactor focus on highest-friction functions
                                 : Trajectory returns toward target band

    section Stage 3 &mdash; Steady-state operation
        Module stable : Trajectory holding within target band
                     : Change-cost estimates within ±25% of actuals
                     : Targets validated as predictive
                     : Quarterly review confirms calibration

    section Stage 4 &mdash; Drift accumulation
        Velocity slowing : Suppression count rising
                        : Estimate-vs-actual variance widening
                        : Trajectory drifting past targets
                        : Architectural review triggered

    section Stage 5 &mdash; Architectural intervention
        Major refactor or rewrite : Debt ledger reviewed
                                 : Target matrix re-calibrated
                                 : Suppressions audited and reduced
                                 : Trajectory reset for next cycle
